var book = {
	"name": "Esther",
	"numChapters": 10,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>This is what happened during the time of Xerxes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12704A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12704A\"></sup> the Xerxes who ruled over 127 provinces<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12704B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12704B\"></sup> stretching from India to Cush:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12704C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12704C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>At that time King Xerxes reigned from his royal throne in the citadel of Susa,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12705D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12705D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and in the third year of his reign he gave a banquet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12706E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12706E\"></sup> for all his nobles and officials. The military leaders of Persia and Media, the princes, and the nobles of the provinces were present.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>For a full 180 days he displayed the vast wealth of his kingdom and the splendor and glory of his majesty.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When these days were over, the king gave a banquet, lasting seven days,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12708F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12708F\"></sup> in the enclosed garden<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12708G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12708G\"></sup> of the king’s palace, for all the people from the least to the greatest who were in the citadel of Susa.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The garden had hangings of white and blue linen, fastened with cords of white linen and purple material to silver rings on marble pillars. There were couches<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12709H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12709H\"></sup> of gold and silver on a mosaic pavement of porphyry, marble, mother-of-pearl and other costly stones.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Wine was served in goblets of gold, each one different from the other, and the royal wine was abundant, in keeping with the king’s liberality.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12710I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12710I\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>By the king’s command each guest was allowed to drink with no restrictions, for the king instructed all the wine stewards to serve each man what he wished.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Queen Vashti also gave a banquet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12712J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12712J\"></sup> for the women in the royal palace of King Xerxes.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>On the seventh day, when King Xerxes was in high spirits<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12713K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12713K\"></sup> from wine,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12713L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12713L\"></sup> he commanded the seven eunuchs who served him—Mehuman, Biztha, Harbona,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12713M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12713M\"></sup> Bigtha, Abagtha, Zethar and Karkas—",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>to bring<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12714N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12714N\"></sup> before him Queen Vashti, wearing her royal crown, in order to display her beauty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12714O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12714O\"></sup> to the people and nobles, for she was lovely to look at.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But when the attendants delivered the king’s command, Queen Vashti refused to come. Then the king became furious and burned with anger.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12715P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12715P\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Since it was customary for the king to consult experts in matters of law and justice, he spoke with the wise men who understood the times<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12716Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12716Q\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and were closest to the king—Karshena, Shethar, Admatha, Tarshish, Meres, Marsena and Memukan, the seven nobles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12717R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12717R\"></sup> of Persia and Media who had special access to the king and were highest in the kingdom.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“According to law, what must be done to Queen Vashti?” he asked. “She has not obeyed the command of King Xerxes that the eunuchs have taken to her.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Memukan replied in the presence of the king and the nobles, “Queen Vashti has done wrong, not only against the king but also against all the nobles and the peoples of all the provinces of King Xerxes.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>For the queen’s conduct will become known to all the women, and so they will despise their husbands and say, ‘King Xerxes commanded Queen Vashti to be brought before him, but she would not come.’",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>This very day the Persian and Median women of the nobility who have heard about the queen’s conduct will respond to all the king’s nobles in the same way. There will be no end of disrespect and discord.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12721S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12721S\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Therefore, if it pleases the king,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12722T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12722T\"></sup> let him issue a royal decree and let it be written in the laws of Persia and Media, which cannot be repealed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12722U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12722U\"></sup> that Vashti is never again to enter the presence of King Xerxes. Also let the king give her royal position to someone else who is better than she.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then when the king’s edict is proclaimed throughout all his vast realm, all the women will respect their husbands, from the least to the greatest.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The king and his nobles were pleased with this advice, so the king did as Memukan proposed.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He sent dispatches to all parts of the kingdom, to each province in its own script and to each people in their own language,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12725V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12725V\"></sup> proclaiming that every man should be ruler over his own household, using his native tongue."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>Later when King Xerxes’ fury had subsided,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12726A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12726A\"></sup> he remembered Vashti and what she had done and what he had decreed about her.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then the king’s personal attendants proposed, “Let a search be made for beautiful young virgins for the king.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Let the king appoint commissioners in every province of his realm to bring all these beautiful young women into the harem at the citadel of Susa. Let them be placed under the care of Hegai, the king’s eunuch, who is in charge of the women; and let beauty treatments be given to them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then let the young woman who pleases the king be queen instead of Vashti.” This advice appealed to the king, and he followed it.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now there was in the citadel of Susa a Jew of the tribe of Benjamin, named Mordecai son of Jair, the son of Shimei, the son of Kish,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12730B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12730B\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>who had been carried into exile from Jerusalem by Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, among those taken captive with Jehoiachin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12731C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12731C\"></sup> king of Judah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12731D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12731D\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Mordecai had a cousin named Hadassah, whom he had brought up because she had neither father nor mother. This young woman, who was also known as Esther,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12732E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12732E\"></sup> had a lovely figure<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12732F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12732F\"></sup> and was beautiful. Mordecai had taken her as his own daughter when her father and mother died.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When the king’s order and edict had been proclaimed, many young women were brought to the citadel of Susa<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12733G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12733G\"></sup> and put under the care of Hegai. Esther also was taken to the king’s palace and entrusted to Hegai, who had charge of the harem.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>She pleased him and won his favor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12734H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12734H\"></sup> Immediately he provided her with her beauty treatments and special food.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12734I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12734I\"></sup> He assigned to her seven female attendants selected from the king’s palace and moved her and her attendants into the best place in the harem.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Esther had not revealed her nationality and family background, because Mordecai had forbidden her to do so.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12735J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12735J\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Every day he walked back and forth near the courtyard of the harem to find out how Esther was and what was happening to her.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Before a young woman’s turn came to go in to King Xerxes, she had to complete twelve months of beauty treatments prescribed for the women, six months with oil of myrrh and six with perfumes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12737K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12737K\"></sup> and cosmetics.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And this is how she would go to the king: Anything she wanted was given her to take with her from the harem to the king’s palace.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>In the evening she would go there and in the morning return to another part of the harem to the care of Shaashgaz, the king’s eunuch who was in charge of the concubines.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12739L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12739L\"></sup> She would not return to the king unless he was pleased with her and summoned her by name.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12739M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12739M\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When the turn came for Esther (the young woman Mordecai had adopted, the daughter of his uncle Abihail<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12740N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12740N\"></sup>) to go to the king,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12740O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12740O\"></sup> she asked for nothing other than what Hegai, the king’s eunuch who was in charge of the harem, suggested. And Esther won the favor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12740P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12740P\"></sup> of everyone who saw her.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>She was taken to King Xerxes in the royal residence in the tenth month, the month of Tebeth, in the seventh year of his reign.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now the king was attracted to Esther more than to any of the other women, and she won his favor and approval more than any of the other virgins. So he set a royal crown on her head and made her queen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12742Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12742Q\"></sup> instead of Vashti.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And the king gave a great banquet,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12743R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12743R\"></sup> Esther’s banquet, for all his nobles and officials.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12743S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12743S\"></sup> He proclaimed a holiday throughout the provinces and distributed gifts with royal liberality.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12743T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12743T\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>When the virgins were assembled a second time, Mordecai was sitting at the king’s gate.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12744U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12744U\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But Esther had kept secret her family background and nationality just as Mordecai had told her to do, for she continued to follow Mordecai’s instructions as she had done when he was bringing her up.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12745V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12745V\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>During the time Mordecai was sitting at the king’s gate, Bigthana and Teresh, two of the king’s officers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12746W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12746W\"></sup> who guarded the doorway, became angry<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12746X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12746X\"></sup> and conspired to assassinate King Xerxes.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But Mordecai found out about the plot and told Queen Esther, who in turn reported it to the king, giving credit to Mordecai.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And when the report was investigated and found to be true, the two officials were impaled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12748Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12748Y\"></sup> on poles. All this was recorded in the book of the annals<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12748Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12748Z\"></sup> in the presence of the king.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12748AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12748AA\"></sup>"
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>After these events, King Xerxes honored Haman son of Hammedatha, the Agagite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12749A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12749A\"></sup> elevating him and giving him a seat of honor higher than that of all the other nobles.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>All the royal officials at the king’s gate knelt down and paid honor to Haman, for the king had commanded this concerning him. But Mordecai would not kneel down or pay him honor.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then the royal officials at the king’s gate asked Mordecai, “Why do you disobey the king’s command?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12751B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12751B\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Day after day they spoke to him but he refused to comply.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12752C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12752C\"></sup> Therefore they told Haman about it to see whether Mordecai’s behavior would be tolerated, for he had told them he was a Jew.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When Haman saw that Mordecai would not kneel down or pay him honor, he was enraged.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12753D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12753D\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Yet having learned who Mordecai’s people were, he scorned the idea of killing only Mordecai. Instead Haman looked for a way<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12754E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12754E\"></sup> to destroy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12754F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12754F\"></sup> all Mordecai’s people, the Jews,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12754G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12754G\"></sup> throughout the whole kingdom of Xerxes.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>In the twelfth year of King Xerxes, in the first month, the month of Nisan, the <i>pur</i><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12755H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12755H\"></sup> (that is, the lot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12755I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12755I\"></sup>) was cast in the presence of Haman to select a day and month. And the lot fell on the twelfth month, the month of Adar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12755J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12755J\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Haman said to King Xerxes, “There is a certain people dispersed among the peoples in all the provinces of your kingdom who keep themselves separate. Their customs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12756K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12756K\"></sup> are different from those of all other people, and they do not obey<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12756L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12756L\"></sup> the king’s laws; it is not in the king’s best interest to tolerate them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12756M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12756M\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>If it pleases the king, let a decree be issued to destroy them, and I will give ten thousand talents of silver to the king’s administrators for the royal treasury.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12757N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12757N\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So the king took his signet ring<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12758O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12758O\"></sup> from his finger and gave it to Haman son of Hammedatha, the Agagite, the enemy of the Jews.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Keep the money,” the king said to Haman, “and do with the people as you please.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then on the thirteenth day of the first month the royal secretaries were summoned. They wrote out in the script of each province and in the language<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12760P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12760P\"></sup> of each people all Haman’s orders to the king’s satraps, the governors of the various provinces and the nobles of the various peoples. These were written in the name of King Xerxes himself and sealed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12760Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12760Q\"></sup> with his own ring.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Dispatches were sent by couriers to all the king’s provinces with the order to destroy, kill and annihilate all the Jews<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12761R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12761R\"></sup>—young and old, women and children—on a single day, the thirteenth day of the twelfth month, the month of Adar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12761S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12761S\"></sup> and to plunder<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12761T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12761T\"></sup> their goods.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>A copy of the text of the edict was to be issued as law in every province and made known to the people of every nationality so they would be ready for that day.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12762U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12762U\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The couriers went out, spurred on by the king’s command, and the edict was issued in the citadel of Susa.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12763V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12763V\"></sup> The king and Haman sat down to drink,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12763W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12763W\"></sup> but the city of Susa was bewildered.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12763X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12763X\"></sup>"
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>When Mordecai learned of all that had been done, he tore his clothes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12764A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12764A\"></sup> put on sackcloth and ashes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12764B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12764B\"></sup> and went out into the city, wailing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12764C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12764C\"></sup> loudly and bitterly.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But he went only as far as the king’s gate,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12765D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12765D\"></sup> because no one clothed in sackcloth was allowed to enter it.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>In every province to which the edict and order of the king came, there was great mourning among the Jews, with fasting, weeping and wailing. Many lay in sackcloth and ashes.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When Esther’s eunuchs and female attendants came and told her about Mordecai, she was in great distress. She sent clothes for him to put on instead of his sackcloth, but he would not accept them.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Esther summoned Hathak, one of the king’s eunuchs assigned to attend her, and ordered him to find out what was troubling Mordecai and why.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Hathak went out to Mordecai in the open square of the city in front of the king’s gate.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Mordecai told him everything that had happened to him, including the exact amount of money Haman had promised to pay into the royal treasury for the destruction of the Jews.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12770E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12770E\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He also gave him a copy of the text of the edict for their annihilation, which had been published in Susa, to show to Esther and explain it to her, and he told him to instruct her to go into the king’s presence to beg for mercy and plead with him for her people.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Hathak went back and reported to Esther what Mordecai had said.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then she instructed him to say to Mordecai,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“All the king’s officials and the people of the royal provinces know that for any man or woman who approaches the king in the inner court without being summoned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12774F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12774F\"></sup> the king has but one law:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12774G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12774G\"></sup> that they be put to death unless the king extends the gold scepter<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12774H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12774H\"></sup> to them and spares their lives. But thirty days have passed since I was called to go to the king.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When Esther’s words were reported to Mordecai,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>he sent back this answer: “Do not think that because you are in the king’s house you alone of all the Jews will escape.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>For if you remain silent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12777I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12777I\"></sup> at this time, relief<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12777J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12777J\"></sup> and deliverance<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12777K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12777K\"></sup> for the Jews will arise from another place, but you and your father’s family will perish. And who knows but that you have come to your royal position for such a time as this?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12777L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12777L\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Esther sent this reply to Mordecai:",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“Go, gather together all the Jews who are in Susa, and fast<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12779M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12779M\"></sup> for me. Do not eat or drink for three days, night or day. I and my attendants will fast as you do. When this is done, I will go to the king, even though it is against the law. And if I perish, I perish.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12779N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12779N\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So Mordecai went away and carried out all of Esther’s instructions."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>On the third day Esther put on her royal robes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12781A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12781A\"></sup> and stood in the inner court of the palace, in front of the king’s<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12781B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12781B\"></sup> hall. The king was sitting on his royal throne in the hall, facing the entrance.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When he saw Queen Esther standing in the court, he was pleased with her and held out to her the gold scepter that was in his hand. So Esther approached and touched the tip of the scepter.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12782C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12782C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then the king asked, “What is it, Queen Esther? What is your request? Even up to half the kingdom,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12783D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12783D\"></sup> it will be given you.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“If it pleases the king,” replied Esther, “let the king, together with Haman, come today to a banquet I have prepared for him.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“Bring Haman at once,” the king said, “so that we may do what Esther asks.”So the king and Haman went to the banquet Esther had prepared.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>As they were drinking wine,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12786E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12786E\"></sup> the king again asked Esther, “Now what is your petition? It will be given you. And what is your request? Even up to half the kingdom,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12786F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12786F\"></sup> it will be granted.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12786G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12786G\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Esther replied, “My petition and my request is this:",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>If the king regards me with favor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12788H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12788H\"></sup> and if it pleases the king to grant my petition and fulfill my request, let the king and Haman come tomorrow to the banquet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12788I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12788I\"></sup> I will prepare for them. Then I will answer the king’s question.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Haman went out that day happy and in high spirits. But when he saw Mordecai at the king’s gate and observed that he neither rose nor showed fear in his presence, he was filled with rage<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12789J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12789J\"></sup> against Mordecai.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12789K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12789K\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Nevertheless, Haman restrained himself and went home.Calling together his friends and Zeresh,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12790L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12790L\"></sup> his wife,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Haman boasted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12791M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12791M\"></sup> to them about his vast wealth, his many sons,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12791N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12791N\"></sup> and all the ways the king had honored him and how he had elevated him above the other nobles and officials.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“And that’s not all,” Haman added. “I’m the only person<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12792O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12792O\"></sup> Queen Esther invited to accompany the king to the banquet she gave. And she has invited me along with the king tomorrow.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But all this gives me no satisfaction as long as I see that Jew Mordecai sitting at the king’s gate.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12793P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12793P\"></sup>”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>His wife Zeresh and all his friends said to him, “Have a pole set up, reaching to a height of fifty cubits,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12794Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12794Q\"></sup> and ask the king in the morning to have Mordecai impaled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12794R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12794R\"></sup> on it. Then go with the king to the banquet and enjoy yourself.” This suggestion delighted Haman, and he had the pole set up."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>That night the king could not sleep;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12795A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12795A\"></sup> so he ordered the book of the chronicles,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12795B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12795B\"></sup> the record of his reign, to be brought in and read to him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>It was found recorded there that Mordecai had exposed Bigthana and Teresh, two of the king’s officers who guarded the doorway, who had conspired to assassinate King Xerxes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12796C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12796C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“What honor and recognition has Mordecai received for this?” the king asked.“Nothing has been done for him,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12797D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12797D\"></sup> his attendants answered.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The king said, “Who is in the court?” Now Haman had just entered the outer court of the palace to speak to the king about impaling Mordecai on the pole he had set up for him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>His attendants answered, “Haman is standing in the court.”“Bring him in,” the king ordered.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When Haman entered, the king asked him, “What should be done for the man the king delights to honor?”Now Haman thought to himself, “Who is there that the king would rather honor than me?”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So he answered the king, “For the man the king delights to honor,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>have them bring a royal robe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12802E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12802E\"></sup> the king has worn and a horse<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12802F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12802F\"></sup> the king has ridden, one with a royal crest placed on its head.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then let the robe and horse be entrusted to one of the king’s most noble princes. Let them robe the man the king delights to honor, and lead him on the horse through the city streets, proclaiming before him, ‘This is what is done for the man the king delights to honor!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12803G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12803G\"></sup>’”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Go at once,” the king commanded Haman. “Get the robe and the horse and do just as you have suggested for Mordecai the Jew, who sits at the king’s gate. Do not neglect anything you have recommended.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So Haman got<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12805H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12805H\"></sup> the robe and the horse. He robed Mordecai, and led him on horseback through the city streets, proclaiming before him, “This is what is done for the man the king delights to honor!”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Afterward Mordecai returned to the king’s gate. But Haman rushed home, with his head covered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12806I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12806I\"></sup> in grief,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and told Zeresh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12807J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12807J\"></sup> his wife and all his friends everything that had happened to him.His advisers and his wife Zeresh said to him, “Since Mordecai, before whom your downfall<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12807K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12807K\"></sup> has started, is of Jewish origin, you cannot stand against him—you will surely come to ruin!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12807L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12807L\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>While they were still talking with him, the king’s eunuchs arrived and hurried Haman away to the banquet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12808M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12808M\"></sup> Esther had prepared."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>So the king and Haman went to Queen Esther’s banquet,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12809A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12809A\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and as they were drinking wine<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12810B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12810B\"></sup> on the second day, the king again asked, “Queen Esther, what is your petition? It will be given you. What is your request? Even up to half the kingdom,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12810C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12810C\"></sup> it will be granted.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12810D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12810D\"></sup>”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then Queen Esther answered, “If I have found favor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12811E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12811E\"></sup> with you, Your Majesty, and if it pleases you, grant me my life—this is my petition. And spare my people—this is my request.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>For I and my people have been sold to be destroyed, killed and annihilated.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12812F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12812F\"></sup> If we had merely been sold as male and female slaves, I would have kept quiet, because no such distress would justify disturbing the king.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>King Xerxes asked Queen Esther, “Who is he? Where is he—the man who has dared to do such a thing?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Esther said, “An adversary and enemy! This vile Haman!”Then Haman was terrified before the king and queen.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The king got up in a rage,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12815G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12815G\"></sup> left his wine and went out into the palace garden.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12815H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12815H\"></sup> But Haman, realizing that the king had already decided his fate,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12815I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12815I\"></sup> stayed behind to beg Queen Esther for his life.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Just as the king returned from the palace garden to the banquet hall, Haman was falling on the couch<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12816J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12816J\"></sup> where Esther was reclining.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12816K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12816K\"></sup>The king exclaimed, “Will he even molest the queen while she is with me in the house?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12816L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12816L\"></sup>As soon as the word left the king’s mouth, they covered Haman’s face.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12816M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12816M\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Harbona,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12817N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12817N\"></sup> one of the eunuchs attending the king, said, “A pole reaching to a height of fifty cubits<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12817O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12817O\"></sup> stands by Haman’s house. He had it set up for Mordecai, who spoke up to help the king.”The king said, “Impale him on it!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12817P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12817P\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So they impaled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12818Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12818Q\"></sup> Haman<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12818R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12818R\"></sup> on the pole<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12818S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12818S\"></sup> he had set up for Mordecai.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12818T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12818T\"></sup> Then the king’s fury subsided.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12818U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12818U\"></sup>"
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>That same day King Xerxes gave Queen Esther the estate of Haman,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12819A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12819A\"></sup> the enemy of the Jews. And Mordecai came into the presence of the king, for Esther had told how he was related to her.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The king took off his signet ring,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12820B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12820B\"></sup> which he had reclaimed from Haman, and presented it to Mordecai. And Esther appointed him over Haman’s estate.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12820C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12820C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Esther again pleaded with the king, falling at his feet and weeping. She begged him to put an end to the evil plan of Haman the Agagite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12821D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12821D\"></sup> which he had devised against the Jews.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the king extended the gold scepter<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12822E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12822E\"></sup> to Esther and she arose and stood before him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“If it pleases the king,” she said, “and if he regards me with favor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12823F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12823F\"></sup> and thinks it the right thing to do, and if he is pleased with me, let an order be written overruling the dispatches that Haman son of Hammedatha, the Agagite, devised and wrote to destroy the Jews in all the king’s provinces.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For how can I bear to see disaster fall on my people? How can I bear to see the destruction of my family?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12824G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12824G\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>King Xerxes replied to Queen Esther and to Mordecai the Jew, “Because Haman attacked the Jews, I have given his estate to Esther, and they have impaled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12825H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12825H\"></sup> him on the pole he set up.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now write another decree<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12826I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12826I\"></sup> in the king’s name in behalf of the Jews as seems best to you, and seal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12826J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12826J\"></sup> it with the king’s signet ring<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12826K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12826K\"></sup>—for no document written in the king’s name and sealed with his ring can be revoked.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12826L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12826L\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>At once the royal secretaries were summoned—on the twenty-third day of the third month, the month of Sivan. They wrote out all Mordecai’s orders to the Jews, and to the satraps, governors and nobles of the 127 provinces stretching from India to Cush.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12827M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12827M\"></sup> These orders were written in the script of each province and the language of each people and also to the Jews in their own script and language.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12827N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12827N\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Mordecai wrote in the name of King Xerxes, sealed the dispatches with the king’s signet ring, and sent them by mounted couriers, who rode fast horses especially bred for the king.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The king’s edict granted the Jews in every city the right to assemble and protect themselves; to destroy, kill and annihilate the armed men of any nationality or province who might attack them and their women and children, and to plunder<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12829O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12829O\"></sup> the property of their enemies.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The day appointed for the Jews to do this in all the provinces of King Xerxes was the thirteenth day of the twelfth month, the month of Adar.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12830P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12830P\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>A copy of the text of the edict was to be issued as law in every province and made known to the people of every nationality so that the Jews would be ready on that day<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12831Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12831Q\"></sup> to avenge themselves on their enemies.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The couriers, riding the royal horses, went out, spurred on by the king’s command, and the edict was issued in the citadel of Susa.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12832R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12832R\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When Mordecai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12833S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12833S\"></sup> left the king’s presence, he was wearing royal garments of blue and white, a large crown of gold<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12833T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12833T\"></sup> and a purple robe of fine linen.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12833U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12833U\"></sup> And the city of Susa held a joyous celebration.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12833V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12833V\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>For the Jews it was a time of happiness and joy,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12834W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12834W\"></sup> gladness and honor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12834X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12834X\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>In every province and in every city to which the edict of the king came, there was joy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12835Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12835Y\"></sup> and gladness among the Jews, with feasting and celebrating. And many people of other nationalities became Jews because fear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12835Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12835Z\"></sup> of the Jews had seized them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12835AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12835AA\"></sup>"
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>On the thirteenth day of the twelfth month, the month of Adar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12836A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12836A\"></sup> the edict commanded by the king was to be carried out. On this day the enemies of the Jews had hoped to overpower them, but now the tables were turned and the Jews got the upper hand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12836B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12836B\"></sup> over those who hated them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12836C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12836C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The Jews assembled in their cities<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12837D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12837D\"></sup> in all the provinces of King Xerxes to attack those determined to destroy them. No one could stand against them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12837E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12837E\"></sup> because the people of all the other nationalities were afraid of them.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And all the nobles of the provinces, the satraps, the governors and the king’s administrators helped the Jews,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12838F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12838F\"></sup> because fear of Mordecai had seized them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12838G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12838G\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Mordecai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12839H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12839H\"></sup> was prominent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12839I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12839I\"></sup> in the palace; his reputation spread throughout the provinces, and he became more and more powerful.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12839J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12839J\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The Jews struck down all their enemies with the sword, killing and destroying them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12840K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12840K\"></sup> and they did what they pleased to those who hated them.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>In the citadel of Susa, the Jews killed and destroyed five hundred men.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They also killed Parshandatha, Dalphon, Aspatha,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Poratha, Adalia, Aridatha,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Parmashta, Arisai, Aridai and Vaizatha,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>the ten sons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12845L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12845L\"></sup> of Haman son of Hammedatha, the enemy of the Jews.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12845M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12845M\"></sup> But they did not lay their hands on the plunder.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12845N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12845N\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The number of those killed in the citadel of Susa was reported to the king that same day.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The king said to Queen Esther, “The Jews have killed and destroyed five hundred men and the ten sons of Haman in the citadel of Susa. What have they done in the rest of the king’s provinces? Now what is your petition? It will be given you. What is your request? It will also be granted.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12847O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12847O\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“If it pleases the king,” Esther answered, “give the Jews in Susa permission to carry out this day’s edict tomorrow also, and let Haman’s ten sons<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12848P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12848P\"></sup> be impaled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12848Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12848Q\"></sup> on poles.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So the king commanded that this be done. An edict was issued in Susa, and they impaled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12849R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12849R\"></sup> the ten sons of Haman.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The Jews in Susa came together on the fourteenth day of the month of Adar, and they put to death in Susa three hundred men, but they did not lay their hands on the plunder.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12850S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12850S\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Meanwhile, the remainder of the Jews who were in the king’s provinces also assembled to protect themselves and get relief<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12851T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12851T\"></sup> from their enemies.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12851U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12851U\"></sup> They killed seventy-five thousand of them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12851V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12851V\"></sup> but did not lay their hands on the plunder.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12851W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12851W\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>This happened on the thirteenth day of the month of Adar, and on the fourteenth they rested and made it a day of feasting<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12852X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12852X\"></sup> and joy.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The Jews in Susa, however, had assembled on the thirteenth and fourteenth, and then on the fifteenth they rested and made it a day of feasting and joy.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>That is why rural Jews—those living in villages—observe the fourteenth of the month of Adar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12854Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12854Y\"></sup> as a day of joy and feasting, a day for giving presents to each other.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12854Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12854Z\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Mordecai recorded these events, and he sent letters to all the Jews throughout the provinces of King Xerxes, near and far,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>to have them celebrate annually the fourteenth and fifteenth days of the month of Adar",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>as the time when the Jews got relief<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12857AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12857AA\"></sup> from their enemies, and as the month when their sorrow was turned into joy and their mourning into a day of celebration.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12857AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12857AB\"></sup> He wrote them to observe the days as days of feasting and joy and giving presents of food<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12857AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12857AC\"></sup> to one another and gifts to the poor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12857AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12857AD\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So the Jews agreed to continue the celebration they had begun, doing what Mordecai had written to them.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>For Haman son of Hammedatha, the Agagite,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12859AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12859AE\"></sup> the enemy of all the Jews, had plotted against the Jews to destroy them and had cast the <i>pur</i><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12859AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12859AF\"></sup> (that is, the lot<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12859AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12859AG\"></sup>) for their ruin and destruction.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12859AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12859AH\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But when the plot came to the king’s attention, he issued written orders that the evil scheme Haman had devised against the Jews should come back onto his own head,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12860AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12860AI\"></sup> and that he and his sons should be impaled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12860AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12860AJ\"></sup> on poles.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12860AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12860AK\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>(Therefore these days were called Purim, from the word <i>pur</i>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12861AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12861AL\"></sup>) Because of everything written in this letter and because of what they had seen and what had happened to them,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>the Jews took it on themselves to establish the custom that they and their descendants and all who join them should without fail observe these two days every year, in the way prescribed and at the time appointed.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>These days should be remembered and observed in every generation by every family, and in every province and in every city. And these days of Purim should never fail to be celebrated by the Jews—nor should the memory of these days die out among their descendants.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So Queen Esther, daughter of Abihail,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12864AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12864AM\"></sup> along with Mordecai the Jew, wrote with full authority to confirm this second letter concerning Purim.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And Mordecai sent letters to all the Jews in the 127 provinces<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12865AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12865AN\"></sup> of Xerxes’ kingdom—words of goodwill and assurance—",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>to establish these days of Purim at their designated times, as Mordecai the Jew and Queen Esther had decreed for them, and as they had established for themselves and their descendants in regard to their times of fasting<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12866AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12866AO\"></sup> and lamentation.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12866AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12866AP\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Esther’s decree confirmed these regulations about Purim, and it was written down in the records."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>King Xerxes imposed tribute throughout the empire, to its distant shores.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12868A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12868A\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And all his acts of power and might, together with a full account of the greatness of Mordecai,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12869B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12869B\"></sup> whom the king had promoted,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12869C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12869C\"></sup> are they not written in the book of the annals<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12869D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12869D\"></sup> of the kings of Media and Persia?",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Mordecai the Jew was second<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12870E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12870E\"></sup> in rank<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12870F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12870F\"></sup> to King Xerxes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12870G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12870G\"></sup> preeminent among the Jews, and held in high esteem by his many fellow Jews, because he worked for the good of his people and spoke up for the welfare of all the Jews.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12870H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12870H\"></sup>"
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;